				<h2>Assigning parameters in perpendicular axes: D-H is a must</h2>
<p>So I was given a course assignment to assign frames and write D-H parameters for this robot <strong>using only 5+1 frames (with Frame $\{5\}$ at $P$ and Frame $\{0\}$ at $O$)</strong>.</p>

<p><a href="https://i.stack.imgur.com/q9Frp.png" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><img src="https://i.stack.imgur.com/q9Frp.png" alt="Original figure"></a></p>

<p>And I assigned them like this:</p>

<p><a href="https://i.stack.imgur.com/kaKk4.png" rel="nofollow noreferrer"><img src="https://i.stack.imgur.com/kaKk4.png" alt="My frames"></a></p>

<p>My question is:
<strong>From Frame $\{1\}$ to Frame $\{2\}$, what are joint distances $a$ and $d$?</strong></p>

<p>The best answer I could get was 0. But obviously it should be zero for one axis and $a_1$ for the other. What's wrong?</p>

<p>I have read a similar question <a href="https://robotics.stackexchange.com/questions/4610/forward-kinematics-d-h-parameters-for-perpendicular-joint-axes">here</a>. But the answer points me to another method which is impossible for me.</p>

