				<p><p>Here are the step that are in my course for using D-H convention:</p>

<h1>Step 1</h1>

<p>Define the z axis of every joint</p>

<h1>Step 2</h1>

<p>Define the origin frame R0 (O<sub>0</sub>, x<sub>0</sub>, y<sub>0</sub>, z<sub>0</sub>)</p>

<h1>Step 3</h1>

<p>For i in [1, n] (<em>n=number of joint</em>)</p>

<h3>Step 3.1</h3>

<p>Define O<sub>i</sub> that belongs to z<sub>i</sub>, and to the common normal to z<sub>i-1</sub> and z<sub>i</sub></p>

<h3>Step 3.2</h3>

<p>Define x<sub>i</sub> such as x<sub>i</sub> is normal to the plan formed by z<sub>i-1</sub> and z<sub>i</sub></p>

<h3>Step 3.3</h3>

<p>Define y<sub>i</sub> such as x<sub>i</sub>, y<sub>i</sub>, z<sub>i</sub> form a right handed coordinate frame</p>

<h2>Step 3.4</h2>

<p>Define the frame of the tool (or the ending point of your arm)</p>

<h3>Step 3.5</h3>

<p>Find the parameters:</p>

<ul>
<li>Q<sub>i</sub> is at the intersection of x<sub>i</sub> and z<sub>i-1</sub></li>
<li>&alpha;_i is the angle between z<sub>i-1</sub>) and z<sub>i</sub> around x<sub>i</sub> axis</li>
<li>a<sub>i</sub> is the distance |Q<sub>i</sub>,O<sub>i</sub>|</li>
<li>d<sub>i</sub> is the distance |O<sub>i-1</sub>, Q<sub>i</sub>| along z<sub>i-1</sub> axis</li>
</ul>

<p>Hope this helps</p>
</p><br>
